      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LA PETITE MAISON (2) has progressed nicely in his last couple of runs. Finished second at Townsville two starts back, then scored by a head last time out over 1100m at this track. Sean Cormack scored on him last time and retains the ride. Well placed, and he can score again. SAILOR'S RUM (3) was an impressive winner over 1050m in a 60 at Rockhampton, leading throughout and putting 5.5 lengths on his rivals. He again draws to advantage, and Wiggins is a key jockey engagement. Hes feared. DETERMINATION (6) is racing well and is close to a win. Presents off a solid placing at Rockhampton over 1200m. DEALING'S DONE (1) resumed in good order in stronger and is a second-up winner. Has more to give, and the 2kg claim is handy. In the mix.",
